Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Separate the @cauliflower{1}(separated into florets) into florets (little trees). Pop the cauliflower florets onto a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and sprinkle on the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1/2}(add less if you don't like heat). Use your hands to rub the seasoning all over. Arrange in one even layer and roast until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the Rice{300} into a #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp}. Bring to the boil and once boiling, stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150}. Lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks, trim the @Pak Choi{1}. Separate the leaves and quarter widthways into roughly 2cm chunks. Trim the @Green Beans{80} and chop into thirds. Zest then cut the @Lime{1/2} into wedges. Roughly chop the @Coriander{1} (stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir-fry the pepper and green beans until beginning to soften and colour, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45} to coat and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the bok choy along with the @Coconut Milk{200} and the @Water for the Sauce{75}. Bring to the boil then turn the heat to medium-low.

Let the curry simmer until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. When the cauliflower is ready, add it to the curry and stir to coat in the sauce. Remove from the heat and stir in the @Soy Sauce{12.5}(add less if you don't need it all). Squeeze in some lime juice. Taste and add more, @?salt{}, @?pepper{} and @?lime juice{} if you feel it needs it. Fluff up the rice and stir in the lime zest and half the coriander.

Share the rice between your bowls and top with the fragrant curry. Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining coriander. Serve the remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!